# Vokler environment variables

- **Production (Next.js server)**: Resolve the backend from **server-only** variables — `API_URL` or `FASTAPI_URL` for `app/api/proxy/route.ts`, and `FRONTEND_APP_KEY` for the upstream `X-App-Key` header. Do not add hardcoded API base URLs; proxy returns 503 if none are set.
- **Browser / client bundle**: Uses `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` only where code runs in the browser (`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` for direct HTTP and WebSockets, `NEXT_PUBLIC_FRONTEND_APP_KEY`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_USE_PROXY=true` to route API calls through same-origin proxy).
- **FastAPI (`api/`)**: Production settings from env (`DATABASE_URL`, `REDIS_URL`, `CORS_ORIGINS`, `APP_ENV=production`, `FRONTEND_APP_KEY`, etc.); no baked-in production URLs.
- **YouTube / yt-dlp**: If downloads fail with bot-check errors on your host IP, set **`YTDLP_COOKIES_FILE`** on the API to an absolute path of a Netscape `cookies.txt` exported while logged into YouTube (mount the file in Docker/Railway). Keep **`yt-dlp`** upgraded (`uv lock --upgrade-package yt-dlp`).

When changing env handling, keep this split: server secrets and internal URLs stay off `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.

## Railway (web service) — common mistakes

- **Typo**: use `NEXT_PUBLIC_FRONTEND_APP_KEY`, not `NEXT_FRONET_APP_KEY`.
- **`RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN` is hostname only** (no `https://`). Either set `API_URL` to `https://${{YourApiService.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}` in one variable, or set hostname only — the proxy prepends `https://` automatically.
- **Do not nest** `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` as `https://${{API_URL}}` when `API_URL` is itself another reference — Railway may not substitute nested references reliably. Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` in one shot, e.g. `https://${{YourApiService.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}` (same expression you would use for the public API URL).
- **Reference the API service name** exactly as shown in Railway (slug), e.g. `vokler-api` not `api` unless your service is literally named `api`.
- **App key from API**: reference `${{YourApiService.FRONTEND_APP_KEY}}` into web `FRONTEND_APP_KEY` or `APP_FRONTEND_KEY` (server-only). The FastAPI app reads `FRONTEND_APP_KEY` / `APP_FRONTEND_KEY`.
- **`NEXT_PUBLIC_*` must exist at Docker/Railpack build time** for the client bundle; define them on the web service so the build step sees them.
- **`ENV` / `RAILWAY_ENVIRONMENT_NAME`**: optional; this Next app does not read `ENV` for API config.
